THREE DAYS OF TECHNICAL SESSIONS (PRELIMINARY)
**********************************************
Wednesday-Friday, June 8-10, Sessions begin at 9:00 am

----Presentations refereed by the Program Committee emphasize open
    systems solutions drawn from practical experience and the latest
    research.
----A parallel track of talks and panels from invited experts provides
    overviews and practical commentary.  Learn techniques for Dynamic
    Storage Allocation, tools and practices that allow you to resolve
    your systems' mysterious behaviors, and what ATM really is and what
    it's good for.  Real-life anecdotes illustrate the security lessons
    to be learned from financial services--electronic commerce won't
    happen unless we learn from the bankers' bleeding-edge
    experiences.  Then, take a critical look at UNIX development with
    respect to whether we are implementing technologies as needed to
    survive the 1990s. 
----Technical Executive Summaries--eight experts will summarize what's
     hot. . .and what's not. . .in their areas of speciality.
----Panels on 25 years of UNIX and ARPANET 
----Included in registration are the Thursday evening Reception, a copy
    of the Proceedings and a copy of the Invited Talks Submitted Notes.


